      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## CP Subsystem \u2014 Operations\n\nAn **operations-focused view** of the CP Subsystem designed for on-call engineers and production monitoring. Where the Overview dashboard answers *\"is something wrong?\"*, this dashboard answers *\"what exactly is wrong and how severe is it?\"*\n\n**What problem does this dashboard address?**\nCP structures are used for distributed coordination: locking shared resources, rate-limiting with semaphores, counting with atomic longs. A failure in any of these layers can cause client threads to block indefinitely or coordination logic to break. This dashboard surfaces the operational signals needed to diagnose and respond quickly.\n\n**Insights this dashboard delivers:**\n\n| Section | Key question | What to act on |\n|---------|-------------|----------------|\n| **Cluster & CP Member Health** | How many members are active? Are any missing? | Missing members > 0: check Docker health; Active members < 3: quorum at risk |\n| **Raft Consensus Health** | Is the commit index advancing? Is available log capacity dropping? Which group has degraded quorum? | Commit lag growing: follower falling behind; Log capacity < 1 000: writes will be rejected soon; Member count < 2: group unavailable |\n| **CP Data Structures** | How many instances of each type are live? Is the destroyed count growing? | Rising destroyed count = structures being re-created \u2014 each creation consumes Raft log entries |\n| **Lock & Semaphore Contention** | Is any lock being acquired at an unusually high rate? Are semaphore permits exhausted? | Acquisition rate spike: contention hot spot; Permits = 0: callers are blocking |\n| **CP Sessions** | Are client sessions heartbeating? Is any session close to expiry? | Flat heartbeat version: hung client; Session near TTL: lock/permits will be auto-released |\n\n**How to use the filters:**\n- **Cluster** \u2014 selects the Hazelcast cluster\n- **CP Group** \u2014 restricts Raft-level panels to specific groups (e.g. isolate `group2` for FencedLock issues)\n\n**Severity guide:**\n- \ud83d\udfe2 All stats green, commit rate steady, no missing members \u2192 healthy\n- \ud83d\udfe1 1 missing member, commit lag < 100, semaphore permits > 0 \u2192 degraded but functional\n- \ud83d\udd34 2+ missing members, group member count \u2264 1, log capacity < 500, permits = 0 \u2192 immediate action required\n\n**Drill-down path:** for deeper Raft internals (snapshot index, log fill rate, apply rate) open **HZ CP \u2014 Raft Internals**."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Cluster & CP Member Health",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 13,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 1
      },
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Reachable CP Members",
      "description": "CP members currently reachable: activeMembers \u2212 missingMembers. Reacts immediately when a member drops. activeMembers alone stays at 5 until formal removal (missing-cp-member-auto-removal-seconds = 8 h).",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 14,
        "w": 6,
        "h": 4
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus"
          },
          "expr": "max(hz_raft_metadata_activeMembers{mc_cluster=\"$cluster\"}) - max(hz_raft_missingMembers{mc_cluster=\"$cluster\"})",
          "legendFormat": "reachable members",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ]
        },
        "orientation": "auto",
        "textMode": "auto",
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "area"
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "decimals": 0,
          "unit": "short",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 0
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 3
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 5
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      }
    },
